&quot;You cannot escape me, even here... &quot;<br>
She growled low, as she pressed back against the chair. Her clenched fists moving to press into the armrests of the chair. She would not give in, not this time. <br>
Soon both voice and pain passed. She relaxed once more as an Idea took shape. A plan of action. She rose and moved to one of the many shelves and from it a small crystal ball was taken. Softly uttered words of an ancient incantation where spoken as her hand passed over its gleaming surface. With each passing the ball began to glow brighter and brighter till it hovered over her palm, no longer resting in it. <br>
&quot;Go now, and find him, He will know what to do with you should he need my services.&quot; Like a shot the ball flew from her and towards the open window. It sailed high into the night sky its destination etched firmly upon it.<br>
An hour or two later it wizzed passed the neriak guards. The jumped towards it but where unable to intercept it as it whisked its way through the foreign quarters, then commons and on to third gate. <br>
The grange guards too attempted to stop it and still it evaded them as it made its way to Khasiraths office. And there it came to rest upon his desk, waiting.. <br>
